 table}}\n|-\n|[[2014 Nigeria Entertainment Awards|2014]]\n|Herself\n|Female Artist of the Year<ref>{{cite web | url=http://tooxclusive.com/news-from-africa/nigeria-entertainment-awards-2014-nominees-list-davido-yemi-alade-others-nominated/ | title=Nigeria Entertainment Awards 2014 Nominees List: Davido, Yemi Alade, Others Nominated | publisher=tooxclusive.com | accessdate=11 September 2014}}</ref>\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[2015 Nigeria Entertainment Awards|2015]]\n|Herself\n|Female artiste of the year\n|{{Won}}\n{{end}}\n\n=== [[City People Entertainment Awards]] ===\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n|2014\n|Herself\n|Female Musician of the Year <ref>{{cite web | url=http://thenet.ng/2014/06/who-won-what-at-city-people-entertainment-awards-2014/ | title=Who won what at City People Entertainment Awards 2014 | publisher=thenet.ng | accessdate=11 September 2014}}</ref>\n|{{nom}}\n{{end}}\n\n===[[MOBO Awards]]===\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n|2014\n|Herself\n|Best African Act<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.mobo.com/voting/best-african-act|title = MOBO Best African Act|date = 2014-09-24|accessdate = 2014-09-24|website = MOBO Best African Act|publisher = mobo.com|last = |first = }}</ref>\n|{{nom}}\n{{end}}\n\n=== YEM Awards ===\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n|2012\n|Herself\n|Female Artiste of the Year<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.360nobs.com/2012/07/young-entertainers-and-music-yem-awards-announces-nominees/|title = YOUNG ENTERTAINERS AND MUSIC [YEM] AWARDS ANNOUNCES NOMINEES. |date = July 2012|accessdate = 2012-07-20|website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref>\n|{{nom}}\n{{end}}\n\n===[[ELOY Awards]]===\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n|2013\n|Herself\n|Most Promising Female<ref>{{cite web|url = http://jaguda.com/2013/11/26/winners-2013-exquisite-lady-year-eloy-2013-awards/|title = All The Winners At The 2013 Exquisite Lady Of The Year (ELOY 2013) Awards|date = 2013-11-26|accessdate = 2013-11-26|website = All The Winners At The 2013 Exquisite Lady Of The Year (ELOY 2013) Awards|publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref>\n|{{nom}}\n{{end}}\n\n===[[WatsUp TV Africa Music Video Awards]]===\n\n{{awards table}}\n!Ref\n|-\n|rowspan=\"7\"|2016\n|rowspan=\"5\"|Want You\n|African Video of the Year\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/entertainment/Checkout-nominees-for-Watsup-Tv-Africa-Music-Video-Awards-473925 |title=Checkout nominees for Watsup Tv Africa Music Video Awards |website=Ghanaweb.com |accessdate=2017-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best African Female Video\n|{{Nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.bellanaija.com/2016/10/yemi-alade-wizkid-diamond-platnumz-cassper-nyovest-others-nominated-for-watsup-tv-africa-music-video-awards-set-to-hold-this-december/ |title=Yemi Alade, Wizkid, Diamond Platnumz, Cassper Nyovest & others Nominated for Watsup TV Africa Music Video Awards set to hold this December |website=Bellanaija.com |date=2016-10-19 |accessdate=2017-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best West African Video\n|{{Nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.todaygh.com/yemi-alade-shatta-wale-nominated-2016-watsup-tv-africa-music-video-awards |title=Yemi Alade, Shatta Wale nominated for 2016 WatsUp TV Africa Music Video Awards \u2013 Today Newspaper |website=Todaygh.com |date=2016-10-05 |accessdate=2017-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best Afro Pop Video\n|{{Nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|last=Nsabimana |first=Eddie |url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201610110051.html |title=Rwanda: Knowles' Video Nominated At Watsup TV Africa Music Video Awards |website=Allafrica.com |date=2016-10-10 |accessdate=2017-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best African Dance Video\n|{{Nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uncova.com/yemi-alade-wizkid-diamond-platnumz-cassper-nyovest--others-nominated-for-watsup-tv-africa-music-video-awards-set-to-hold-this-december |title=Yemi Alade, Wizkid, Diamond Platnumz, Cassper Nyovest & others Nominated for Watsup TV Africa Music Video Awards set to hold this December \u2013 BellaNaija |website=Uncova.com |date=2016-10-19 |accessdate=2017-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Ferrari\n|Best African Traditional Video\n|{{Nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pulse.com.gh/music/wamva-2016-bisa-kdei-shatta-wale-sarkodie-wizkid-flavour-others-nominated-id5557711.html |title=WAMVA 2016: Bisa Kdei, Shatta Wale, Sarkodie, Wizkid, Flavour, others nominated \u2013 Music |language= German|website=Pulse.com.gh |date=2016-10-29 |accessdate=2017-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n{{end}}\n\n===[[The Headies]]===\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n|[[The Headies 2019|2019]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Herself\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Best Performer\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|[[The Headies 2018|2018]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|2017\n|Best Performer\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[The Headies 2016|2016]]\n|Herself\n|Artiste of the Year\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|[[The Headies 2015|2015]]\n|Herself\n|[[The Headies Award for Hip Hop World Revelation of the Year|Hip Hop World Revelation of the Year]]\n|{{Won}}\n{{end}}\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of Nigerian musicians]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Official website|https://www.yemialadeofficial.com/}}\n{{Yemi Alade}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Alade, Yemi}}\n[[Category:Nigerian female pop singers]]\n[[Category:University of Lagos alumni]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Abia State]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Ondo State]]\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Nigerian rhythm and blues singers]]\n[[Category:Yoruba musicians]]\n[[Category:Igbo musicians]]\n[[Category:English-language singers from Nigeria]]\n[[Category:Yoruba-language singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Nigerian singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century women singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Yemi Alade\n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = Yemi Alade.png\n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| native_name_lang = Igbo\n| birth_name       = Yemi Eberechi Alade\n| alias            = <!-- nicknames are not considered stage names --> \n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1989|03|13}}\n| birth_place      = [[Abia State]], [[Nigeria]]\n| origin           = \n| death_date       = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date 1st) -->\n| death_place      = \n| genre            = {{hlist|[[Afropop]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]|[[World music|world]]}}\n| occupation       = {{hlist|Singer|songwriter}}\n| instrument       = Vocals\n| years_active     = 2005\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|Effyzzie|[[Universal Music Group|Universal]]}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Selebobo]]|Rotimi Keys|GospelOnDeBeatz|[[DJ Coublon]]}}\n| website          = {{URL|yemialadeofficial.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Yemi Eberechi Alade''' (born 13 March 1989), known professionally as '''Yemi Alade''', is a Nigerian [[Afropop]] singer and songwriter. She gained prominence after winning the ''Peak Talent Show'' in 2009, After which she made an advancement in her music career and released a single \"Ghen ghen Love\". In 2014, Alade was signed to Effyzzie Music Group and is best known for her hit single \"[[Johnny (Yemi Alade song)|Johnny]]\" which was one of her prior singles under the label.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2014/08/new-sexy-singers-loose/ | title=New, sexy singers on the loose | publisher=vanguardngr.com | accessdate=7 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2014/07/yemi-alade-tours-kenya/ | title=Yemi Alade tours Kenya | publisher=vanguardngr.com | accessdate=7 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://dailyindependentnig.com/2013/12/looks-helped-career-yemi-alade/ | title=My looks have helped my career \u2013Yemi Alade | publisher=dailyindependentnig.com | accessdate=7 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nYemi Eberechi Alade was born in [[Abia State]], Nigeria, to James Alade and Helen Uzoma. Her father was a police commissioner of Yoruba descent while her mother is of Igbo descent, resulting in her being referred to as the Yoruba-Igbo girl. A native of Ondo State, South West, Nigeria, Alade is the fifth born of seven children in her family. She went to St. Savior British Primary School and later attended Victory Grammar School in [[Lagos]]. Alade studied geography at the [[University of Lagos]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thefader.com/2016/11/09/yemi-alade-interview-tumbum-mama-africa|title=How Yemi Alade Hustled Her Way To Become The Queen Of Afrobeats|work=The FADER|access-date=2018-08-30|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Music career ==\n===2014\u20132016: ''King of Queens'' and ''Mama Africa''===\nAlade's debut studio album ''[[King of Queens (album)|King of Queens]]'' was released on October 2, 2014. Alade collaborated with producers such as [[Selebobo]], Sizzle Pro, Shady Bizniz, Philkeyz, Young D, GospelOnDeBeatz, [[DIL (musician)|DIL]], [[OJB Jezreel]], Mr Chidoo, Fliptyce, EL Mcee and Beat Nation. The album was preceded by the singles \"[[Johnny (Yemi Alade song)|Johnny]]\", \"Tangerine\" and \"Kissing\". It features [[guest appearances]] and skits from [[Bovi]], [[R2Bees]], [[Phyno]], [[Chidinma]], DIL, [[Selebobo]] and [[Diamond Platnumz]].<ref>{{cite web|title=YEMI ALADE UNVEIL THE COVER OF HER DEBUT ALBUM \"KING OF QUEENS\"|url=http://www.tmzafrica.com/yemi-alade-unveil-the-cover-of-her-debut-album-king-of-queens/|publisher=TMZ Africa|accessdate=9 October 2014|date=8 October 2014}}</ref> Alade promoted the album by touring several African countries, including Ghana, Kenya and South Africa.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Anozie|first1=Egole|title=Yemi Alade tours Kenya|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2014/07/yemi-alade-tours-kenya/|publisher=Vanguard|accessdate=8 October 2014|date=11 July 2014}}</ref> The album's deluxe edition was released in November 2014; it contains French versions of songs originally performed in English. The cover art for the deluxe edition was unveiled on 21 October 2014.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ayomide|first1=Tayo|title=Singer To Release 'King Of Queens' Deluxe Version|url=http://pulse.ng/music/yemi-alade-singer-to-release-king-of-queens-deluxe-version-id3213295.html|publisher=Pulse|accessdate=3 March 2015|date=21 October 2014}}</ref> According to the music platform A Nation of Billions, ''King of Queens'' sold over 100,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Akua Ofei |title=HOW YEMI ALADE RUN THE WORLD |url=https://nationofbillions.com/meeting-mama-africa-yemi-alade |publisher=A Nation of Billions |accessdate=23 February 2019 |date=10 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nAlade's second studio album ''[[Mama Africa (Yemi Alade album)|Mama Africa]]'' was released on March 25, 2016.<ref name=\"Pulse Nigeria 214\">{{cite web |title=Singer to release 2nd album \"Mama Africa\", March 2016 |url=https://www.pulse.com.gh/entertainment/music/yemi-alade-singer-to-release-2nd-album-mama-africa-march-2016/y3s34br |publisher=Pulse Nigeria |accessdate=18 October 2019 |date=October 28, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191018232938/https://www.pulse.com.gh/entertainment/music/yemi-alade-singer-to-release-2nd-album-mama-africa-march-2016/y3s34br |archive-date=18 October 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Alade disclosed its title was ''Mama Africa'' and said it would focus on the strengths and weaknesses of an African woman.<ref name=\"Pulse Nigeria 214\" /> The album combines elements of [[Afropop]], [[highlife]], [[R&B]], [[coup\u00e9-d\u00e9cal\u00e9]], [[hip-hop]] and [[pop music|pop]].<ref name=\"Circulation Magazine\">{{cite web |author1=Adaobi Nezianya |title=Mama Africa by Yemi Alade |url=http://www.circulation-mag.com/2016/08/mama-africa-yemi-alade/ |accessdate=21 February 2019 |publisher=Circulation Magazine |date=6 August 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190222151935/http://www.circulation-mag.com/2016/08/mama-africa-yemi-alade/ |archive-date=22 February 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"The Fader 142\">{{cite web |author1=Alex Macpherson |title=How Yemi Alade Hustled Her Way To Become The Queen Of Afrobeats |url=https://www.thefader.com/2016/11/09/yemi-alade-interview-tumbum-mama-africa |publisher=The Fader |accessdate=18 October 2019 |date=November 9, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191018232937/https://www.thefader.com/2016/11/09/yemi-alade-interview-tumbum-mama-africa |archive-date=18 October 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Alade said recording the album was a struggle because she was constantly traveling to different countries everyday.<ref name=\"The Fader 142\"/> She also said she recorded the album to \"capture all of Africa on one CD\".<ref name=\"The Fader 142\"/> Alade told ''[[The Fader]]'' magazine she collaborated with artists from West Africa, East Africa and South Africa.<ref name=\"The Fader 142\"/> She enlisted GospelOnDeBeatz, [[DJ Coublon]], [[Selebobo]], Philkeyz, BeatsByEmzo, [[Masterkraft (producer)|Masterkraft]], Rotimi Keys and Mr. Chidoo to produce the album.<ref name=\"Life\">{{cite web|last1=Sakoh|first1=Makale|title=Yemi Alade Releases Her Sophomore Album \"Mama Africa\"|url=http://life.guardian.ng/2016/03/yemi-alade-releases-her-sophomore-album-mama-africa/|accessdate=12 April 2016|date=25 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160507191944/http://life.guardian.ng/2016/03/yemi-alade-releases-her-sophomore-album-mama-africa/|archive-date=7 May 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Mama Africa'' features guest appearances from [[P-Square]], [[Sarkodie (rapper)|Sarkodie]], [[Sauti Sol]], [[Flavour N'abania]], Rotimi Keys, [[DJ Arafat]] and [[Selebobo]].<ref name=\"Life\"/> It was made available for pre-order on [[iTunes]] a week before its official release.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Solanke|first1=Abiola|title=''Mama Africa'' album available for pre-order|url=http://pulse.ng/buzz/yemi-alade-mama-africa-album-available-for-pre-order-id4816300.html|publisher=Pulse Nigeria|accessdate=12 April 2016|date=12 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160405223847/http://pulse.ng/buzz/yemi-alade-mama-africa-album-available-for-pre-order-id4816300.html|archive-date=5 April 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Alade announced that proceeds from the sale of the album will go to the Feed a Child charity initiative.<ref name=\"Life\"/>  The album's deluxe edition was released on April 6, 2016, and features collaborations with South African musicians [[Bucie]] and [[AKA (rapper)|AKA]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Solanke|first1=Abiola|title=Singer set to release deluxe edition of her \"Mama Africa\" album|url=http://pulse.ng/buzz/yemi-alade-singer-set-to-release-deluxe-edition-of-her-mama-africa-album-id4879117.html|publisher=Pulse Nigeria|accessdate=12 April 2016|date=4 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160414202013/http://pulse.ng/buzz/yemi-alade-singer-set-to-release-deluxe-edition-of-her-mama-africa-album-id4879117.html|archive-date=14 April 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Mama Africa'' charted in Germany, Malaysia and France.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Akua Ofei |title=How Yemi Alade Run the World |url=https://nationofbillions.com/meeting-mama-africa-yemi-alade |publisher=A Nation of Billions |accessdate=18 October 2019 |date=May 10, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190505133853/https://nationofbillions.com/meeting-mama-africa-yemi-alade |archive-date=5 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== 2017\u2013present: ''Black Magic'' and ''Woman of Steel'' ===\nAlade's third studio album ''[[Black Magic (Yemi Alade album)|Black Magic]]'' was released on December 15, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pulse.ng/entertainment/music/yemi-alade-singer-releases-third-album-black-magic/17h6f47|title=Singer releases third album \"Black Magic\"|date=2017-12-15|website=Pulse Nigeria|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref> A follow-up to her 2017 EP ''Mama Afrique'', the album features guest appearances from [[Falz]] and [[Olamide]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.okayafrica.com/yemi-alade-just-dropped-a-new-album-black-magic/|title=Yemi Alade's New Album 'Black Magic' Is Here|date=2017-12-15|website=OkayAfrica|language=en|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> ''Black Magic'' was made available for pre-order in November 2017.<ref name=\"Native 4\">{{cite web |author1=Fisayo Okare |title= Yemi Alade's Upcoming Third Studio Album \"Black Magic\" is now available for pre-order|url=https://thenativemag.com/music/yemi-alade-keeps-going-mama-africa-third-studio-album-black-magic/ |website=Native |accessdate=24 March 2020 |date=November 20, 2017}}</ref> Prior to disclosing the album's title, Alade posted the acronym BM on social media and wanted her fans to guess its meaning.<ref name=\"Native 4\" /> The album was produced by [[DJ Coublon]], Vtek, [[Sarz]], [[Krizbeatz]], Young D, Sess, Fliptyce, IAmBeat, Philkeyz, 2Kriss and Echo.<ref>{{cite web |title=Yemi Alade\u2019s Third Studio Album \u201cBlack Magic\u201d is available now |url=https://www.bellanaija.com/2017/12/yemi-alade-black-magic-go-down/ |website=BellaNaija |date=December 18, 2017}}</ref> It was supported by the previously released singles \"Knack Am\", \"Single & Searching\" and \"Heart Robber\". The album received generally negative reviews from music critics, who panned its lyrics and Alade's songwriting.<ref name=\"360nobs 1\">{{cite web |author1=Wilfred Okiche |title=Album Review: Black Magic- Yemi Alade |url=https://www.360nobs.com/2018/06/album-review-black-magic-yemi-alade/ |website=360nobs |accessdate=26 March 2020 |date=June 25, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Pulse Nigeria 7\">{{cite web |title=Of all Yemi Alade\u2019s three albums, \u201cBlack Magic\u201d has the least power |url=https://www.pulse.ng/entertainment/music/album-review-of-all-yemi-alades-three-albums-black-magic-has-the-least-power/nvbrkq3 |website=Pulse Nigeria |accessdate=24 March 2020 |date=December 15, 2017}}</ref> \n\nIn July 2019, Alade became the first African female artist to reach one million subscribers on YouTube.<ref>{{cite web |title=Yemi Alade Is the First African Female Artist To Get A Million Subscribers On YouTube |url=https://www.okayafrica.com/yemi-alade-youtube-million-subscribers-first-african-female-artist/ |publisher=OkayAfrica |accessdate=8 September 2019 |date=July 2, 2019}}</ref> Her song \"Johnny\" currently holds the YouTube record for the most watched African Female music video of all time.<ref>{{cite web |title=Top 10 Most Viewed African Music Videos on Youtube |url=https://listwand.com/top-10-most-viewed-african-music-videos-on-youtube/ |publisher=Listwand |accessdate=December 13, 2019}}</ref> Alade was featured on \"Don't Jealous Me\", a track from [[Beyonc\u00e9]]'s soundtrack album ''[[The Lion King: The Gift]]''. She appeared on the track alongside [[Mr Eazi]] and [[Tekno (musician)|Tekno]].She was also featured on a track \"My Power from the album alongside [[Busiswa]] and other artists. \ufffc\ufffc''[[Rolling Stone]]'' magazine revealed that Alade also recorded a verse for an earlier version of \"My Power\" in June.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Elais Leight |title=Inside Beyonc\u00e9\u2019s Bold Bet to Get Americans to Listen to African Music |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/how-beyonce-made-the-lion-king-the-gift-861019/ |publisher=Rolling Stone |accessdate=20 July 2019 |date=19 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nAlade released her fourth studio album ''[[Woman of Steel (album)|Woman of Steel]]'' on August 30, 2019. Alade describes the album as a \"buffet with different kinds of meals and drinks\".<ref name=\"The Star 33\" /> She named the album ''[[Woman of Steel (album)|Woman of Steel]]'' to reflect her tough veneer to command the same degree of respect as her male counterparts.<ref name=\"OkayAfrica 22\">{{cite web |author1=Damola Durosomo |title=Yemi Alade\u2019s Journey to Becoming a \u2018Woman of Steel\u2019 |url=https://www.okayafrica.com/yemi-alade-journey-to-becoming-a-woman-of-steel-interview-new-album-nigerian-music/ |website=OkayAfrica |accessdate=19 March 2020 |date=August 30, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203012541/https://www.okayafrica.com/yemi-alade-journey-to-becoming-a-woman-of-steel-interview-new-album-nigerian-music/ |archive-date=3 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Moreover, she derived the title after coming to the realization that she is her own superhero.<ref name=\"Business Daily 1\">{{cite web |title=Yemi Alade Releases New \u2018Woman of Steel\u2019 Album |url=https://www.businessdailyafrica.com/lifestyle/music/Yemi-Alade-releases-new--Woman-of-Steel--album/3815720-5324902-ki5tdv/index.html |website=Business Daily |accessdate=19 March 2020 |date=October 25, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191106030909/https://www.businessdailyafrica.com/lifestyle/music/Yemi-Alade-releases-new--Woman-of-Steel--album/3815720-5324902-ki5tdv/index.html |archive-date=6 November 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Musically, ''[[Woman of Steel (album)|Woman of Steel]]'' is an [[Afrobeats]] record that incorporates elements of [[R&B]] and [[highlife]].<ref name=\"Pulse Nigeria 712\">{{cite web |author1=Motolani Alake |title=Yemi Alade: 'Woman of Steel' is best album yet [Album Review] |url=https://www.pulse.ng/entertainment/music/yemi-alade-woman-of-steel-is-best-album-yet-album-review/me1dc4j |website=Pulse Nigeria |accessdate=19 March 2020 |date=September 3, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319225725/https://www.pulse.ng/entertainment/music/yemi-alade-woman-of-steel-is-best-album-yet-album-review/me1dc4j |archive-date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Motolani Alake |title=Yemi Alade releases 15-track new album, \u2018Woman of Steel\u2019 |url=https://www.pulse.ng/entertainment/music/yemi-alade-releases-15-track-new-album-woman-of-steel/9dv496f |website=Pulse Nigeria |accessdate=21 March 2020 |date=30 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190914064704/https://www.pulse.ng/entertainment/music/yemi-alade-releases-15-track-new-album-woman-of-steel/9dv496f |archive-date=14 September 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The album primarily explores topics such as love, socio-politics and poverty.<ref name=\"Pulse Nigeria 712\" /> Alade spent three years recording the album and said it would be released on August 30, 2019.<ref name=\"The Star 33\">{{cite web |author1=Elizabeth Musyimi |title='Woman of Steel' up for Grammy's \u2014 Yemi Alade |url=https://www.the-star.co.ke/sasa/word-is/2019-10-18-woman-of-steel-up-for-grammys--yemi-alade/ |website=The Star |accessdate=18 March 2020 |date=18 October 2019}}</ref> The album's cover art features Alade wearing a headcap inspired by the [[Nefertiti Bust]] artwork.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Damola Durosomo |title=Watch Yemi Alade's New Music Video for 'Give Dem' |url=https://www.okayafrica.com/yemi-alade-drops-two-new-singles-from-her-forthcoming-album-woman-of-steel-give-dem-music-video/ |website=OkayAfrica |accessdate=20 March 2020 |date=August 21, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320180702/https://www.okayafrica.com/yemi-alade-drops-two-new-singles-from-her-forthcoming-album-woman-of-steel-give-dem-music-video/ |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Artists featured on ''Woman of Steel'' include [[Rick Ross]], [[Duncan Mighty]], [[Ang\u00e9lique Kidjo]] and [[Funke Akindele]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pulse.ng/entertainment/music/yemi-alade-to-release-her-album-woman-of-steel-next-week-releases-two-singles/9hgl6l5|title=Yemi Alade to release her album, \u2018Woman of Steel\u2019 next week and releases two singles|date=2019-08-21|website=Pulse Nigeria|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref> In an interview with ''[[The Star (Kenya)|The Star]]'' newspaper, Alade said some of the songs that made the album were recorded the previous year while others were recorded in August.<ref name=\"The Star 33\" />\n\nIn September 2019, Alade signed a multi-year licensing deal with Universal Music Africa (UMA) and UMG France. UMA will serve as the exclusive worldwide record partner for Alade while UMG France will serve as the international rollout partner for all of her releases under the label.<ref>{{cite web |title=Singer Yemi Alade signs licensing deal with Universal Music Group |url=https://punchng.com/singer-yemi-alade-signs-licensing-deal-with-universal-music-group/ |website=The Punch |accessdate=28 March 2020 |date=September 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Tours ==\nYemi Alade has gone on three world tours following her studio albums:\n*Mama Africa Tour<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bellanaija.com/2017/04/yemi-alade-kicks-off-her-mama-africa-world-tour-in-paris-selling-out-the-le-trianon-see-photos/|title=Yemi Alade Kicks Off her Mama Africa World Tour in Paris selling out the Le Trianon {{!}} See Photos|last=BellaNaija.com|date=2017-04-08|website=BellaNaija|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20170405-eye-africa-yemi-alade-mama-africa-anc-close-ranks-behind-zuma-gambia-legislative-election|title=Eye on Africa - Nigerian afropop star Yemi Alade in Paris on 'Mama Africa' World Tour|date=2017-04-06|website=France 24|language=en|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref>\n* Black Magic Tour<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tooxclusive.com/video-yemi-alade-black-magic-world-tour-diary-episode-1/|title=[Video] Yemi Alade - Black Magic World Tour Diary (Episode 1) \u00ab tooXclusive|date=2018-07-26|website=tooXclusive|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref>\n* Woman of Steel Tour<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.today.ng/multimedia/photo/yemi-alade-kicks-wos-tour-ethiopia-pictures-video-260304|title=Yemi Alade kicks off \"WOS\" World Tour in Ethiopia \u2014 in pictures & video|last=TODAY|date=2019-10-29|website=TODAY|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n=== Albums ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[King of Queens (album)|King of Queens]]''\n|\n* Released